                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="text-gray-300 text-sm mt-3 p-3 bg-gray-800/50 rounded border border-gray-700">
                            Powerful pattern: safely access nested property <span class="text-cyan-300">(?.)span>, provide fallback if nullish <span class="text-purple-300">(??)</span>.
                        </div>

                        <ProTip>
                            <div>🌟 <strong>Best pattern for nested access:</strong></div>
                            <div class="pl-2 border-l-2 border-yellow-500/30 space-y-0.5 mt-1">
                                <div class="font-mono text-[10px]">const city = user?.address?.city ?? 'Unknown'</div>
                                <div class="font-mono text-[10px] mt-1"><span class="text-gray-400">// Safe and readable:</span></div>
                                <div class="font-mono text-[10px]">// 1. Safely navigates nested properties (?.)</div>
                                <div class="font-mono text-[10px]">// 2. Provides fallback if undefined (??)</div>
                                <div class="font-mono text-[10px]">// 3. Preserves valid falsy values like 0, false, ""</div>
                            </div>
                        </ProTip>
                    </MethodCard>
