                                    </div>
                                    <div class="font-mono text-[10px]">
                                        <span class="text-red-300">null</span> <span class="text-purple-300">||</span> <span class="text-green-300">'default'</span>
                                        <span class="text-gray-400 ml-3">→ 'default'</span>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="font-mono text-[10px]">
                                        <span class="text-red-300">0</span> <span class="text-purple-300">||</span> <span class="text-green-300">10</span>
                                        <span class="text-gray-400 ml-3">→ 10 <span class="text-red-300">(watch out!)</span></span>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="text-gray-300 text-sm mt-3 p-3 bg-gray-800/50 rounded border border-gray-700">
                            Short-circuits: if left is truthy, <strong>doesn't evaluate right side</strong>. Used for defaults, but watch out for 0, false, "".
                        </div>

                        <ProTip>
                            <div>⚠️ <strong>Default values (with gotcha):</strong></div>
                            <div class="pl-2 border-l-2 border-yellow-500/30 space-y-0.5 mt-1">
                                <div class="font-mono text-[10px]">const name = username || 'Guest'</div>
